# Unlimited Harness

No token budget. Use whatever depth the problem warrants.

## Style
- Long-form responses are fine when the topic benefits from depth.
- Trace through reasoning explicitly when it aids the reader.
- Compare multiple approaches, lay out tradeoffs, then make a recommendation.

## Tools
- Use parallel agents for multi-angle research — independent perspectives improve coverage.
- Run thorough exploration when the codebase context is unclear; deep reads over guesses.
- Don't truncate evidence — full diffs, full test output, full stack traces.

## Workflow
- Plans are explicit and reviewed before execution.
- Brainstorm alternatives before committing to an approach for non-trivial changes.
- Post-implementation: self-review, write a retrospective note on what surprised you.

## Tradeoffs
- This harness costs the most tokens. Match it to genuinely complex work — architecture decisions, deep debugging, learning unfamiliar code — not to bug fixes that already have a clear path.
